Package fr.cnrs.iees.graph

Interface EdgeSet<E extends Edge>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The Edge subclass used to construct the graph
    N - The Node subclass connected by Edges of class E
    All Superinterfaces:
    fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Graph<N,​E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ALGraph, TreeGraph
    public interface EdgeSet<E extends Edge>
extends fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable

    A Graph is defined as a G=(N,E,f) where N is a set of nodes, E a set of edges connecting the nodes, and f the incidence function mapping every edge to a pair of nodes.

    This interface is used to represent E, the set of edges of a graph.

    Some graph implementations (e.g. Tree) may have no use for this interface since their edges are implicit.

    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 14 mai 2019
